Caption: A whirlwind 24 hours in Brussels 🇧🇪As hubby had a meeting there, (he always does the hard work while I have the fun bits !), I thought I may as well take a trip down memory lane. We lived here for a couple of years a few years ago and I regularly used to mooch around, visiting various flea markets, art galleries and street cafés. Generally experiencing the Belgian way of life, totally different to our Dutch life as you can imagine. I polished up on my very poor French, stayed with some lovely old friends in their magnificent house and had the most fabulous IG meet up with . I don’t think I could have packed much more in, time well spent as they say ☺️.Today it’s back out on Old Dutch, a long cycle, a nice coffee and maybe a visit to a Kringloop, who knows.Whatever your plans, have a very happy Wednesday.

Caption: El gato Scottish Fold se caracteriza indudablemente por sus orejitas caídas. Ellas son pequeñas en comparación con el tamaño de su cabeza y están dobladas hacia adelante.Además tienen un aspecto curioso, ya que al ser su cabeza redonda, pareciera que tuviera un gorrito de baño encima bajándolas. El doblez de sus orejas puede variar.Algunos gatos presentan solo un pliegue, otros dos y otros tres. Donde los gatos con orejas de 3 pliegues pueden ser preferidos en las exposiciones por tener más pureza 😻
translate caption: ['The Scottish Fold cat is undoubtedly characterized by its floppy ears. They are small compared to the size of his head and are bent forward. They also have a curious appearance, since their heads are round, it seems that they have a bathing cap on them. The fold of their ears can vary. Some cats have only one fold, others two and others three. Where cats with 3-fold ears can be preferred in shows for having more purity 😻']
